programme.title: The Long Chase
programme.desc: Governor Yan is killed and his guard Fan identifies Kou as the assassin by his signature weapon, a dart. Kou is listed as a wanted man, but managed to escape arrest with the help of the innkeeper's daughter.

programme.title: Songfest
programme.desc: Shot on location at Taiwan's beautiful Sun-Moon Lake, it's the turbulent romance of a passionate tea picker and a debonair fisherman.

programme.title: Monkey Kung Fu
programme.desc: Wei Chun is a cocky young man sentenced to jail for killing a man in a fight. One day, Wei Chun picks a fight with an old man that turns out to be the master of monkey style kung fu and as they become friends.

programme.title: The Three Smiles
programme.desc: A talented scholar, Bo Hu, is attracted by the pretty maid, Qiu Xiang. In order to get close to her and win her love, he disguises as a servant to work in the same household.

programme.title: The Fantastic Magic Baby
programme.desc: The story is about the legendary Monkey King teams up with Goddess of Mercy and the Dragon Girl to battle the child god Hung Hai-erh, son of the Ox Demon to rescue Tang Tseng, the Holy Pilgrim.

programme.title: Forever And Ever
programme.desc: Lo Wei helms this poetic romance that proves a perfect showcase for Ivy Ling Po's incredible talents, as a young scholar manipulated into marrying a nobleman's reluctant daughter.

programme.title: Les Belles
programme.desc: Linda Lin Dai and Fanny Fan join the dancing troupe of Kao Pao-shu. Linda and Kao's son Peter Chen, manager of the troupe, have misunderstandings and dislike each other.

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung
programme.desc: Emperor Chien Lung goes incognito to mix with his people and understand their needs. He encounters many strange things along the way, including being arrested and nearly beheaded. Who will save him?

programme.title: King Gambler
programme.desc: A pre-cursor to the gambling craze that swept Asian Cinema, here cardsharp is pitted against cardsharp in a kung-fu fuelled duel of fists and wits to become king of the casino.

programme.title: Madam White Snake
programme.desc: Linda Lin Dai is perfect as Pak Su-cheng, the stunning snake goddess who assumes a womanly form so that she can taste the pleasures of a human life!

programme.title: Bat Without Wings
programme.desc: A notorious rapist-murderer murders a famed swordsman's fiancee and frames another, forcing the two aggreived heroes to team up with a beautiful swordswoman in search of the truth.

programme.title: The Dream Of The Red Chamber
programme.desc: The fruitless love between Bao Yu and Dai Yu. The marriage of this beloved couple seems next to impossible, as the ruthless mother of Bao Yu deliberately arranges the marriage of his son with another lady.

programme.title: The Magnificent Trio
programme.desc: A group of farmers who are being oppressed by the local magistrates kidnap one of the magistrate's daughter in the hope of being heard by the authorities.

programme.title: The 5 Billion Dollar Legacy
programme.desc: Three girls travel to Japan to collect an unexpected inheritance, only to be met by three guys there to do the same. So begins a vicious battle to receive what was promised them.

programme.title: Shaolin Intruders
programme.desc: A gripping combination of eye-popping martial arts and thrilling detective work, sees monk Lei Hsin storm the Shaolin temple to clear his friend, accused of murdering.

programme.title: The Lotus Lamp
programme.desc: A bizarre yet beautiful fantasy, starring Lin Dai as a goddess who falls in love with Cheng Pei Pei's scholar. 14 years later their son seeks to unravel the mystery.

programme.title: Crippled Avengers
programme.desc: Chang Cheh follows his international hit, The Five Venoms with a popular sequel about blind, deaf, footless and child-like kung-fu fighters who brilliantly train to take their revenge.

programme.title: The Empress Dowager
programme.desc: In 5000 years of Chinese history, there was never a more fascinating woman than the dragon lady of the Ching Dynasty, also the Empress Dowager, who was the power behind the throne for the last half of the 19th century.

programme.title: Men From The Monastery
programme.desc: In the Ming Dynasty, Wu San Gui betrays his people to the Qing officials and recruits fighters from all backgrounds. When they start attacking the Shaolin Monastery, the disciples have to fight against the enemies.

programme.title: Hong Kong Nocturne
programme.desc: This film showcases the little seen dancing talents of celebrated kung-fu swordswoman Cheng Pei-Pei, as one of three girls dancing their way to the top.

programme.title: Heaven Sword & Dragon Sabre 2
programme.desc: Only by bringing together the powerful Heaven Sword and mighty Dragon Sabre can six martial arts sects struggling for supremacy be saved in this thrilling sequel to Chu Yuan's hit.

programme.title: The Shepherd Girl

programme.title: Asia-Pol
programme.desc: Asiapol agent Yang Ming Xuan trails a shipment of contraband gold being delivered to gang leader, George Eaton. He enlists the help of a Chinese woman who is trying to avenge her sister.

programme.title: Little Hero
programme.desc: An orphan, Little Bastard is taken on and trained as a fighter by a hermit. When he grows up, he feels he is old enough to go out and look for his parents.

programme.title: Secret Service Of Imperial...

programme.title: Flying Guillotine 2

programme.title: Crazy Shaolin Disciples

programme.title: Return Of The Crazy Bumpkins

programme.title: Forbidden Tales Of Two Cities

programme.title: The Brave Archer 3
programme.desc: Guo Jing and Huang Rong go to Iron Palm Peak to search for the Book of Wumu. The chief of Iron Palm discovers their visit, and seriously injures Huang.

programme.title: The Mighty One

programme.title: Emperor Chien Lung And The...

programme.title: Clan Of The White Lotus

programme.title: The Mirror And The Lichee
programme.desc: The curious title refers to two props that signal a happy beginning to what develops into a tragic love story between the scholar and a local beauty.
